MatterName: Prohibiting silencing political dissent.
MatterTitle:
A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York,
	 in relation to prohibiting the Mayor and any elected official from using the Police Department to limit dissemination of political speech and from employing the political process,
	 or political influence inherent with the elective office,
	 for the purpose of silencing political dissent.

MatterName: Creating disclosure requirements related to mobile telephone service.
MatterTitle:
A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York,
	 in relation to creating disclosure requirements related to mobile telephone service.

MatterName: Auto industry to stop enticing consumers to purchase a new car while still paying a remaining balance on an old car.
MatterTitle: Resolution calling upon the automobile industry to stop enticing consumers to purchase a new car while still paying a remaining balance on an old car loan that exceeds the old car’s trade-in value.

MatterName: Creating elder care information centers.
MatterTitle:
A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York,
	 in relation to creating elder care information centers where persons can receive information on programs and services pertinent to senior citizens.

MatterName: Prohibiting the sale of sharpened samurai swords or other large swords of a similar kind.
MatterTitle:
A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York,
	 in relation to prohibiting the sale of sharpened samurai swords or other large swords of a similar kind.

MatterName: Requiring that schools provide instruction on domestic violence and sexual assault in grades 7-12.
MatterTitle: Resolution calling upon the State to pass a law requiring that schools provide instruction on domestic violence and sexual assault in grades 7-12.

MatterName: Application of selected requirements of the NYC Campaign Finance Program.
MatterTitle:
A Local Law to amend the charter and the administrative code of the city of New York,
	 in relation to application of the public disclosure requirements of the New York City Campaign Finance Program to all candidates for the offices of mayor,
	 public advocate,
	 comptroller,
	 borough president,
	 and member of the city council.

MatterName: Requirements of the campaign finance program for city elections.
MatterTitle:
A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York,
	 in relation to the requirements of the campaign finance program for city elections.

MatterName:
Vehicle and Traffic Law to require national background check and fingerprinting of all applicants to drive limousine,
	 for-hire cars and taxicab.
MatterTitle:
Resolution calling upon the Legislature of the State of New York to amend the Vehicle and Traffic Law to require national background checks and fingerprinting of all applicants to drive limousines,
	 for-hire cars and taxicabs licensed by the New York City Taxi and Limousine Commission.

MatterName:
Approving the granting of an exemption from real property taxes,
	 Congregation Avnei Pinchos known as 5822 17th St,
	 NY.
MatterTitle:
Resolution approving the granting of an exemption from real property taxes pursuant to section 420-a of the real property tax law,
	 for the parcel owned by Congregation Avnei Pinchos known as 5822 17th Avenue in the City of New York,
	 borough of Brooklyn,
	 being designated on the tax map as block 5503,
	 lot 52 and 53 in such borough,
	 and the cancellation of taxes,
	 fines,
	 penalties and interest remaining unpaid,
	 and the making of appropriate correction of the subject assessment roll,
	 if,
	 upon accepting and reviewing the application or renewal application for such exemption,
	 the Department of Finance is satisfied that such corporation or association would otherwise be entitled to such exemption if it had filed such application for exemption by the appropriate taxable status date,
	 in accordance with Chapter 326 of the laws of 2003.

MatterName: Prohibit the sale and use of any device that converts liquid alcohol into vapor form enabling its inhalation.
MatterTitle: Resolution calling on the State Legislature to amend the Alcoholic Beverage Control and Penal Laws to prohibit the sale and use of any device that converts liquid alcohol into vapor form enabling its inhalation.

MatterName: Prohibiting Gift Certificate Charges
MatterTitle:
Resolution calling upon the State Legislature to amend the General Business Law in relation to prohibiting businesses from selling gift certificates,
	 or issuing store credits,
	 containing expiration dates or from adding dormancy fees,
	 latency fees,
	 or any other administrative fees or service charges that have the effect of reducing the total amount of the gift certificate or store credit face value.
